Why should we use service in kubernetes cluster?
For example: 
    In k8s cluster lets take two applications App1 and App2 
App1 wants to connect with App2, Here it can use IP address for communicaiton with App2 , But there is a problem, 
The problem is the IP address of the application 2 can change because in k8s cluster parts are epumeral (only a short period of time.)
They are designed for recreation often so IP is going to change, Now App1 can not keep track of those changing IPs dynamically.
its very difficult.

So when these IP can change:
=============================
  1) Lets say there is a node which is running this pod, we are tacking out that node for maitanance, what we should do , 
evict all the pods running on this node, shecuduled them into different node.in that case IP will change. 

  2) The secound senario, we may have autoscalling in place, so lets say now we have three instances on Pods
After some time it can become 5 again then the load decreases it can become 2 and 3 After some time the IP address can be 
completely different.

  3) Its very common , when we do new release, right lets say currently we are running version 001 for App2 we prepare release 002.
when we rollout this new feature using deployment, lets say all pods are terminated and replaced

These are the reasons why IP address of a pod can change, Thats the reason App1 can not directly talk to App2 using its IP address, Which 
is going to chane very ofetn. 
That's the reason what kubernetes has done it came up with concept service.

So the service here its not resource like a pod, service will never go down,  In the background service is simply a network rule 
with stable IP address.

How it works the app1 will not directly talk to App2 , instead it talk to its service on its IP address or using service name.

What are the features offered by service: 
=========================================
For example to achive high availability and scalability, we added more replicase, those pods can be load balanced, That can be done 
by a service.

1) provide stable network endpoints 
2) Load balancing set of pods 
3) can expose application to the out side world
















